        "category": "class",
        "description": {
            "value": "<p>Your ripostes can deflect attacks back at their source.</p>\n<p>You can use @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.Opportune Riposte] with a trigger of \"A foe outside of your reach critically fails an attack roll against you\" in addition to its usual trigger.</p>\n<p>When you use Opportune Riposte with this new trigger against a ranged attack, your Strike deflects some of the triggering effect back toward its source. Compare the result of your attack roll to the AC of the triggering foe. On a hit, you deal the normal amount of damage for your Strike, but the damage type changes to that of the triggering attack.</p>\n<p>For instance, if you used Opportune Riposte to deflect a @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Ray of Frost], your Strike would deal cold damage instead of its normal damage type.</p>"
        },
